Analysis

About

This storyboard investigates the tweets from the official Twitter accounts for each NBA Western Conference team. (Abbreviations of team names are used in visualizations.) Where analysis of a single team is performed, the content of the San Antonio Spurs (SAS) account is used.

Temporal Count: From when did the extracted data come?

The first tweet shown is at 2018-01-04 11:56:22, and the last tweet shown is at 2018-01-04 11:56:22. The team with the most tweets during this time is POR (3246). The team with the least is DET (3199).

NOTE: Only tweets occuring between the last “first” tweet and the first “last” tweet across all entities are shown. In reality, some timelines have tweets going back farther and/or occurring more recently in time. (The actual first tweet occurs at 2017-01-20 17:16:26, and the actual last tweet occurs at 2018-03-04 02:43:57.) Nonetheless, tweets are truncated across entities in order to “normalize” the data.

Temporal Count: Which hours of the day are the most common for each team?

Most activity occurs at the end of the day. This makes sense–nearly all NBA games occur at night.

Word (Single) Frequency: What are the most common words for each team?

It’s evident that team accounts reference themselves a lot. (After all, these accounts are used primarily for promotional purposes.) Aside from team-level references, the team accounts mention team players a lot, which is not suprising.
